{"metadata":{"title":"Machine Translation","open_time":"2012-02-29 1740","soft_close_time":"2012-03-06 2201","hard_close_time":"2012-03-06 2201","duration":"0","retry_delay":"10","maximum_submissions":"10","modified_time":"1330765213865","parameters":{"show_explanations":{"question":"before_soft_close_time","option":"before_soft_close_time","score":"before_soft_close_time"}},"maximum_score":"4"},"preamble":{},"data":{"question_groups":{"question_group":[{"@attributes":{"select":"1"},"preamble":{},"question":{"@attributes":{"id":"3a4ff27029bc5a781e0797ed0899994c","type":"GS_Short_Answer_Question_Simple"},"metadata":{"parameters":{"rescale_score":"1","type":"numeric"}},"data":{"text":"<p>Suppose we have the following training corpus for English-to-Turkish translation.<\/p>\n\n<p><pre>\nEnglish:   children sing         sing melodies           happy children\nTurkish:   \u00c3\u00a7ocuklar s\u00c3\u00b6ylerim     melodileri s\u00c3\u00b6ylerim     mutlu \u00c3\u00a7ocuklar\n<\/pre><\/p>\n\n<p>Use the $$EM$$ algorithm to find the translation probaility $$t(\u00c3\u00a7ocuklar|children)$$ after $$TWO$$ complete $$EM$$ iterations.\nAssume uniform initial probailities and round your response to two decimal places (e.g., 0.41).<\/p>","explanation":{},"option_groups":{"@attributes":{"randomize":"true"},"option_group":{"@attributes":{"select":"all"},"option":{"@attributes":{"id":"218c3e2ea573255a79031a3a5be69981","selected_score":"1","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"0.73","explanation":{}}}}}}},{"@attributes":{"select":"1"},"preamble":{},"question":{"@attributes":{"id":"9117d44e61f748efeeb87dfe568da41d","type":"GS_Choice_Answer_Question"},"metadata":{"parameters":{"rescale_score":"1","choice_type":"radio"}},"data":{"text":"<p>Consider the following English-French translation. Blue lines represent the one-to-many (or null) mapping from English to French. Red lines represent the one-to-many (or null) mapping from French to English.<\/p>\n<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q1b.png\"\nalt=\n\"English: Italians do not like milk in coffee.\nFrench: Les Italiens n'aiment pas le lait dans le caf\u00c3\u00a9.\nMappings from English to French:\nItalians-->Les, Italiens; do-->(null); not-->n', pas; like-->aiment; milk-->le, lait; in-->dans; coffee-->le, caf\u00c3\u00a9.\nMappings from French to English:\nLes-->(null); Italiens-->Italians; n'-->do, not; aiment-->like; pas-->(null); le-->(null); lait-->milk; dans-->in; le-->(null); caf\u00c3\u00a9-->coffee.\"> \n<p>Which of the following represents the $$intersection$$ between the English-to-French and French-to-English alignment maps?<\/p>","explanation":{},"option_groups":{"@attributes":{"randomize":"true"},"option_group":{"@attributes":{"select":"all"},"option":[{"@attributes":{"id":"19a7a8d64f2e2a855815280a065efaab","selected_score":"1","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q2y.png\" height=\"150\" alt=\"matrix with y labels: Italians, do, not, like, milk, in, coffee; x labels: Les, Italiens, n', aiment, pas, le, lait, dans, le, caf\u00c3\u00a9. Following cells are filled in: (Italians,Italiens), (not,n'), (like,aiment), (milk,lait), (in,dans), (coffee,caf\u00c3\u00a9)\">","explanation":{}},{"@attributes":{"id":"c39984be11a3c11dc7cbb37603afe95a","selected_score":"0","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q2n1.png\" height=\"150\" alt=\"matrix with y labels: Italians, do, not, like, milk, in, coffee; x labels: Les, Italiens, n', aiment, pas, le, lait, dans, le, caf\u00c3\u00a9. Following cells are filled in: (Italians,Italiens), (do,n'), (not,n'), (like,aiment), (milk,lait), (in,dans), (coffee,caf\u00c3\u00a9)\">","explanation":{}},{"@attributes":{"id":"430ea65095e6c0d5e01842296ca0a491","selected_score":"0","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q2n2.png\" height=\"150\" alt=\"matrix with y labels: Italians, do, not, like, milk, in, coffee; x labels: Les, Italiens, n', aiment, pas, le, lait, dans, le, caf\u00c3\u00a9. Following cells are filled in: (Italians,Italiens), (not,n'), (not,pas), (like,aiment), (milk,lait), (in,dans), (coffee,caf\u00c3\u00a9)\">","explanation":{}},{"@attributes":{"id":"6b7b517dc6dd199ed47fdb2b73a70632","selected_score":"0","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q2n3.png\" height=\"150\" alt=\"matrix with y labels: Italians, do, not, like, milk, in, coffee; x labels: Les, Italiens, n', aiment, pas, le, lait, dans, le, caf\u00c3\u00a9. Following cells are filled in: (Italians,Les), (Italians,Italiens), (not,n'), (like,aiment), (milk,le), (milk,lait), (in,dans), (coffee,le), (coffee,caf\u00c3\u00a9)\">","explanation":{}}]}}}}},{"@attributes":{"select":"1"},"preamble":{},"question":{"@attributes":{"id":"7a0a63722599f4fe70c6ba54abc42fd0","type":"GS_Short_Answer_Question_Simple"},"metadata":{"parameters":{"rescale_score":"1","type":"numeric"}},"data":{"text":"<p>Suppose we are translating the following French sentence:<\/p>\n\n<pre>Je ne me suis pas souvenu que nous l'avons vu.<\/pre>\n\n<p>A good translation of this might be \"I didn't remember that we saw it.\" But let's suppose we have the following set of \nreference translations and a single translation candidate.<\/p>\n<pre>\n\tRef1:\tI did not remember that we have seen it.\n\tRef2:\tI did not remember that we had seen it.\n\tRef3:\tI had not remembered that it we have seen.\n\n\tCand:\tI not me remember that we saw it.\n<\/pre>\n<p>Calculate <b>BLEU-2<\/b> for this candidate. (Use the definition of <b>BLEU<\/b> from the lecture slides&mdash;slightly different than as presented in the textbook&mdash;and round your response to two decimal places, e.g., 0.67.)<\/p>","explanation":{},"option_groups":{"@attributes":{"randomize":"true"},"option_group":{"@attributes":{"select":"all"},"option":{"@attributes":{"id":"9b805bebe9d813cc56ef20e634885778","selected_score":"1","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"0.19","explanation":{}}}}}}},{"@attributes":{"select":"1"},"preamble":{},"question":{"@attributes":{"id":"e0933569d7162c78ff70d71b97082822","type":"GS_Short_Answer_Question_Simple"},"metadata":{"parameters":{"rescale_score":"1","type":"regexp"}},"data":{"text":"<p>Consider the following English sentence and its translation into Turkish.<\/p>\n<img src=\"images\/MTquiz\/q4.png\"\nalt=\n\"English: Ahmet read the letter Ali wrote.\nTurkish: Ahmet, Ali'nin yazdigi mektubu okudu.\nPhrase mappings: (Ahmet,Ahmet), (read,okudu), (the letter,mektubu), (Ali,Ali'nin), (wrote,mektubu)\">\n<p>What is the complete set of distortions? (Enter as space-separated values, e.g., \"0 1 2 0 -1\".)<\/p>","explanation":{},"option_groups":{"@attributes":{"randomize":"true"},"option_group":{"@attributes":{"select":"all"},"option":{"@attributes":{"id":"65764e373eadcd612134c8386908ceb6","selected_score":"1","unselected_score":"0"},"text":"\/^[^\\-0-9]*(0)[^\\-0-9]+(3)[^\\-0-9]+(\\-2)[^\\-0-9]+(\\-3)[^\\-0-9]+(0)[^\\-0-9]*$\/","explanation":{}}}}}}}]}}}